      <scopecontent id="aspace_2f3c69dda56ff9caf7023f6e5b0a91d4">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The William R. Burt Papers consist of copies of charts and memoranda prepared by the War Department relating to the availability and condition of aircraft and their allocation to the various theaters of operation to efficiently utilize air power during World War II. The collection was the gift of William R. Burt in 1994.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_bf98c849614cc6f647f6f060c9e7685e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>William R. Burt served as staff officer to General Hoyt S. Vandenberg during 1940-1946, as well as Secretary of Air Staff for the USAAF in Washington, D.C. He also served as duty officer for the Allied Expeditionary Air Force and as Chief of Policy and Liaison for Air Division U.S. Control Council, Berlin.</p>  
      </bioghist>
